    "explanation": "\n<p><strong>Given:</strong></p>\n\n<p><p>Monthly income of Ramesh = ₹45,000</p></p>\n<p><p>Monthly expenditure on housing = 25%</p></p>\n<p><p>Monthly expenditure on transportation = 10%</p></p>\n\n<p>To calculate the percentage of an amount, use the formula $X\\% = \\frac{X}{100}$.</p>\n\n<p>Let $X$ be the total monthly expenditure of Ramesh on housing and transportation.</p>\n<p>$ X = (25\\% + 10\\%) \\text{ of } 45000 $</p>\n<p>$ X = 35\\% \\text{ of } 45000 $</p>\n<p>$ X = \\left( \\frac{35}{100} \\times 45000 \\right) =  \\left( 35 \\times 450 \\right) = 15750 $</p>\n<p><strong>∴ The required total monthly expenditure on housing and transportation is ₹15,750.</strong></p>",
