    "explanation": "<p><p>The total number of students who appeared = 1800</p></p>\n<p><p>The total number of students who passed = 800</p></p>\n<p><p>Students appeared from Section C = 100°</p></p>\n<p><p>Percent of students passed from Section C = 25%</p></p>\n\n<p><strong>Concept:</strong></p>\n\n<p><p>$X\\% = \\frac{X}{100}$</p></p>\n<p><p>A circle has a total of 360°</p></p>\n\n<p><strong>Calculation:</strong></p>\n<p>Let the total number of failed students from Section C be $X$.</p>\n<p>The total number of students who appeared from Section C is:</p>\n<p>$ \\left(\\frac{100}{360}\\right) \\times 1800 = 500 $</p>\n<p>The total number of students who passed from Section C is:</p>\n<p>$ \\left(\\frac{25}{100}\\right) \\times 800 = 200 $</p>\n<p>Therefore, the total number of failed students from Section C is:</p>\n<p>$ X = 500 - 200 = 300 $</p>\n<p><strong>∴ The required result is 300.</strong></p>",
