        "content": "10"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "4",
        "content": "9"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "3"
    ],
    "explanation": "<p>We need to find the average of India's FDI (Foreign Direct Investment) from 1992 to 1995, rounded to the nearest whole number.</p>\n<p><strong>Steps to Calculate:</strong></p>\n<p>FDI in 1992 = 5.7</p>\n<p>FDI in 1993 = 10.15</p>\n<p>FDI in 1994 = 12.16</p>\n<p>FDI in 1995 = 10.22</p>\n<p>Add all the FDI amounts: $ 5.7 + 10.15 + 12.16 + 10.22 = 38.23 $</p>\n<p>Divide the total by 4 (number of years) to find the average: $ \\frac{38.23}{4} = 9.5575 $</p>\n<p>Round 9.5575 to the nearest integer, which is 10.</p>\n<p>Therefore, the correct answer is 10.</p>",
